==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shot-clog
<hw>Shot"-clog`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person tolerated
only because he pays the shot, or reckoning, for the rest of the
company, otherwise a mere clog on them.</def> <mark>[Old
Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou common <qex>shot-clog</qex>, gull of all companies.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shote</ent>⟦br⟧
